<div class="hero"><div class="hero-inner">
<div class="badge"><span class="badge-dot"></span>For executives</div>
<h1 class="hero-h">AI for VPs of Marketing: <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">the tactical playbook.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">As VP Marketing, you are accountable for pipeline contribution and brand. AI is the leverage that lets a small team operate like a larger one. Here is the tactical playbook for what to deploy first, second, third.</p>
</div></div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">The deployment sequence</span><h2 class="h2">First 90 days</h2>
    <p class="body"><strong>Weeks 1-4: Foundation.</strong> Shared Marketing Claude Project with ICP, voice guide, top-performing content, brand positioning. Every team member starts using it for drafts.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>Weeks 5-8: Content production scale.</strong> AI-enabled content workflows. Output goes from N pieces/month to 2-3N pieces/month with same headcount.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>Weeks 9-12: Cross-channel coordination.</strong> Email, social, paid, content all operating off the same shared brain. Voice and message consistency improves dramatically.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>Beyond 90 days: Optimization.</strong> A/B testing with AI hypothesis generation, lifecycle marketing automation, ABM-at-scale.</p>
    </div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Team-level fluency requirements</span><h2 class="h2">What every marketer should know</h2>
    <p class="body">How to set up and use a shared Claude Project. Foundational.</p>
    <p class="body">How to write a marketing brief in Claude. See <a href="/how-to-write-a-marketing-brief-with-claude" style="color:#00C853;">our guide</a>.</p>
    <p class="body">How to edit AI content so it does not sound like AI. See <a href="/how-to-edit-ai-content-without-it-sounding-like-ai" style="color:#00C853;">our editorial guide</a>.</p>
    <p class="body">How to use AI-generated outputs as drafts, not finished work.</p>
    </div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Metrics that matter</span><h2 class="h2">How to prove the AI rollout worked</h2>
    <p class="body"><strong>Content output per FTE.</strong> Should double in 90 days.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>Time-from-brief-to-published.</strong> Should compress 50-60%.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>Brand voice consistency.</strong> Measurable via internal audit.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>Pipeline contribution.</strong> Lagging indicator but the one CEOs care about.</p>
    </div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><p class="body" style="margin-top:2rem;font-style:italic;color:#8FAF8F;">&mdash; Bill Colbert, <a href="/about" style="color:#00C853;text-decoration:none;">Treetop Growth Strategy</a></p></div></section>
